data.meta_description: Che Runqiu (Chinese  pinyin Ch Rnqi Cantonese Yale Ch Yeuhnchu born 25 October 1990 in Guangzhou, China), is a Chineseborn Hong Kong footballer who currently plays as a midfielder and defender for Hong Kong Premier League club Southern. Che joined Hong Kong First Division League club
data.text:
Club career

Che joined Hong Kong First Division League club Tai Po in 2009. He started developed as a regular first team member in the 2011â€“12 season as he featured a total of 19 matches in the season. Che joined fellow First Division club Southern on 21 June 2013.

On 11 July 2017, Southern announced via Facebook that they had brought back Che.

International career

On 21 June 2013, Che was selected into the 28-men Hong Kong under-23 training squad for the 2013 East Asian Cup.
